---
import ToolPage from '../layouts/ToolPage.astro';
---
<ToolPage
  title="Prompt Builder, turn a vague idea into a clear prompt | KB Cafe"
  description="Answer a few questions, task, audience, goal, tone, length, format, and get a structured prompt that actually works. Beginner-friendly, deterministic, client-side. Nothing uploaded."
  path="/prompt-builder"
  eyebrow="AI Explained · Tool"
  h1="Prompt Builder"
  tagline="Stop typing vague one-liners. Fill in the six things every good prompt needs and watch a clear, structured prompt assemble itself. No prompt-engineering jargon required."
>
  <div class="pb-form">
    <div class="pb-field"><label>1 · What do you want it to do?</label>
      <div class="pb-row">
        <select id="task"></select>
        <input id="subject" type="text" placeholder="a landing page for a yoga studio" />
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="pb-field"><label>2 · Who is it for? <span class="pb-opt">(audience)</span></label>
      <input id="audience" type="text" placeholder="busy parents who are new to yoga" /></div>
    <div class="pb-field"><label>3 · What should it accomplish? <span class="pb-opt">(goal)</span></label>
      <input id="goal" type="text" placeholder="get them to book a free intro class" /></div>
    <div class="pb-grid">
      <div class="pb-field"><label>4 · Tone</label><select id="tone"></select></div>
      <div class="pb-field"><label>5 · Length</label><select id="length"></select></div>
      <div class="pb-field"><label>6 · Format</label><select id="format"></select></div>
    </div>
    <div class="pb-field"><label>Extra context or an example <span class="pb-opt">(optional)</span></label>
      <textarea id="extra" rows="2" placeholder="e.g. our studio focuses on gentle, beginner-friendly classes"></textarea></div>
  </div>

  <div class="pane" style="margin-top:8px">
    <div class="pane-label"><span>Your prompt</span></div>
    <textarea id="out" class="ta" readonly spellcheck="false"></textarea>
  </div>
  <button class="btn-copy" id="copy" type="button" style="margin-top:12px"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><rect x="9" y="9" width="11" height="11" rx="2"/><path d="M5 15V5a2 2 0 0 1 2-2h10"/></svg><span class="lbl">Copy prompt</span></button>
  <p class="pb-note">Assembled from your answers, nothing invented. Tweak any field and the prompt updates live. Paste it into any AI chat.</p>

  <Fragment slot="explainer">
    <h2>A good prompt is just answered questions</h2>
    <p>
      Beginners type <em>&ldquo;write me a landing page&rdquo;</em> and get mush, because they left every important
      decision blank. A strong prompt isn&rsquo;t a magic formula; it&rsquo;s simply one that answers the questions
      the model would otherwise have to guess: what to do, who for, why, in what tone, how long, and in what shape.
      This builder asks those questions and assembles the answer into a clean, structured prompt, so you learn the
      shape by filling it in.
    </p>
    <p class="note">
      The builder doesn&rsquo;t call an AI and doesn&rsquo;t invent anything, it just structures what <em>you</em>
      provide into the format models respond to best. Everything runs in your browser.
    </p>

    <h2>FAQ</h2>
    <details class="faq"><summary>Will this write the prompt for me?</summary>
      <p>It structures your answers into a well-formed prompt. The substance is yours; the builder handles the shape, the part beginners usually miss.</p>
    </details>
    <details class="faq"><summary>Why these six fields?</summary>
      <p>They&rsquo;re the decisions a vague prompt leaves to chance. See exactly what gets guessed when they&rsquo;re missing in the <a href="/prompt-simulator">Prompt Simulator</a>.</p>
    </details>
    <details class="faq"><summary>Is anything uploaded?</summary>
      <p>No. Assembly is entirely client-side, so your inputs stay on your device.</p>
    </details>

    <h3>Related</h3>
    <p>See why blanks hurt in the <a href="/prompt-simulator">Prompt Simulator</a>, check your draft with the <a href="/prompt-linter">Prompt Linter</a>, or take the <a href="/learn-prompting">Learn Prompting</a> course.</p>
  </Fragment>
</ToolPage>

<style>
  .link-btn{font-family:var(--font-mono);font-size:11px;font-weight:700;letter-spacing:.06em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--coral);background:none;border:0;cursor:pointer}
  .link-btn:hover{color:var(--coral-deep);text-decoration:underline}
  .pb-form{display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:15px}
  .pb-field{display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:7px}
  .pb-field label{font-family:var(--font-mono);font-size:12px;font-weight:700;letter-spacing:.04em;color:var(--ink)}
  .pb-opt{color:var(--ink-soft);font-weight:500;text-transform:none}
  .pb-row{display:grid;grid-template-columns:180px 1fr;gap:10px}
  .pb-grid{display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(3,1fr);gap:14px}
  .pb-field input,.pb-field select,.pb-field textarea{font-family:var(--font-body);font-size:14.5px;border:1.5px solid var(--line);border-radius:11px;padding:11px 13px;background:var(--cream);color:var(--ink);outline:0;width:100%}
  .pb-field select{font-family:var(--font-mono);font-size:13.5px}
  .pb-field input:focus,.pb-field select:focus,.pb-field textarea:focus{border-color:var(--ink)}
  .ta{min-height:160px}
  .pb-note{font-family:var(--font-mono);font-size:11.5px;color:var(--ink-soft);margin-top:8px;opacity:.9}
  @media(max-width:560px){.pb-row{grid-template-columns:1fr}.pb-grid{grid-template-columns:1fr}}
</style>

<script is:inline>
  const $ = (id) => document.getElementById(id);
  const TASKS = [
    { v: 'Write', role: 'expert copywriter' }, { v: 'Code', role: 'senior software engineer' },
    { v: 'Research', role: 'thorough research analyst' }, { v: 'Analyze', role: 'sharp analyst' },
    { v: 'Brainstorm', role: 'creative strategist' }, { v: 'Summarize', role: 'concise editor' },
    { v: 'Explain', role: 'patient teacher' }, { v: 'Rewrite', role: 'skilled editor' },
  ];
  const TONES = ['(no preference)', 'professional', 'friendly', 'playful', 'authoritative', 'warm', 'neutral', 'witty', 'persuasive'];
  const LENGTHS = ['(no preference)', 'one line', 'a short paragraph', 'about 150 words', 'about 300 words', 'comprehensive'];
  const FORMATS = ['(no preference)', 'prose', 'bullet points', 'numbered steps', 'a table', 'markdown with headings', 'JSON'];

  function fill(sel, arr) { $(sel).innerHTML = arr.map(o => `<option value="${typeof o === 'string' ? o : o.v}">${typeof o === 'string' ? o : o.v}</option>`).join(''); }
  fill('task', TASKS); fill('tone', TONES); fill('length', LENGTHS); fill('format', FORMATS);

  function build() {
    const task = $('task').value, role = (TASKS.find(t => t.v === task) || {}).role || 'expert';
    const subject = $('subject').value.trim(), audience = $('audience').value.trim(), goal = $('goal').value.trim();
    const tone = $('tone').value, length = $('length').value, format = $('format').value, extra = $('extra').value.trim();
    const none = (v) => !v || v.startsWith('(');

    const article = /^[aeiou]/i.test(role.trim()) ? 'an' : 'a';
    let p = `You are ${article} ${role}.`;
    p += ` ${task} ${subject || '[describe what you want]'}`;
    if (audience) p += ` for ${audience}`;
    p += '.';
    if (goal) p += ` The goal is to ${goal}.`;
    if (!none(tone)) p += ` Use a ${tone} tone.`;
    if (!none(length)) p += ` Keep it ${length}.`;
    if (!none(format)) p += ` Return the result as ${format}.`;
    if (extra) p += `\n\nContext: ${extra}`;
    $('out').value = p;
  }
  const FIELDS = ['task', 'subject', 'audience', 'goal', 'tone', 'length', 'format', 'extra'];
  function syncUrl() {
    const p = new URLSearchParams();
    FIELDS.forEach(id => { const v = $(id).value.trim(); if (v && !v.startsWith('(')) p.set(id, v); });
    const qs = p.toString();
    history.replaceState(null, '', qs ? location.pathname + '?' + qs : location.pathname);
  }
  // hydrate from a shared deep link
  const params = new URLSearchParams(location.search);
  FIELDS.forEach(id => { if (params.has(id)) $(id).value = params.get(id); });
  FIELDS.forEach(id => $(id).addEventListener('input', () => { build(); syncUrl(); }));
  $('copy').addEventListener('click', async () => {
    if (!$('out').value) return;
    try { await navigator.clipboard.writeText($('out').value); } catch { return; }
    const b = $('copy'); b.classList.add('done'); b.querySelector('.lbl').textContent = 'Copied!';
    setTimeout(() => { b.classList.remove('done'); b.querySelector('.lbl').textContent = 'Copy prompt'; }, 1600);
  });
  build();
</script>
